======================================================================
AMENABILITY OBSTRUCTION: WHY NO INVARIANT MEASURE
======================================================================

H vs F decomposition comparison:

  p=7: F_p = 13.00, log(F_p) = 2.5649
  Mode contributions to log(F):
    k=1 (odd ): Q=5.0489, log(1+Q)=1.7999 (70.2%)
    k=2 (even): Q=0.3080, log(1+Q)=0.2685 (10.5%)
    k=3 (odd ): Q=0.6431, log(1+Q)=0.4966 (19.4%)
  Total log(F) = 2.5649
  If H were product-measurable: H ∝ F (exact)
  Actual: H has alpha_2, alpha_3 corrections (NON-product)
  This is the 'non-measurability': the partition function
  cannot be decomposed into independent spectral modes.

  p=11: F_p = 89.00, log(F_p) = 4.4886
  Mode contributions to log(F):
    k=1 (odd ): Q=12.3435, log(1+Q)=2.5910 (57.7%)
