    k=3 (odd ): Q=1.4487, log(1+Q)=0.8956 (20.0%)
    k=4 (even): Q=0.3533, log(1+Q)=0.3025 (6.7%)
    k=5 (odd ): Q=0.5830, log(1+Q)=0.4593 (10.2%)
  Total log(F) = 4.4886
  If H were product-measurable: H ∝ F (exact)
  Actual: H has alpha_2, alpha_3 corrections (NON-product)
  This is the 'non-measurability': the partition function
  cannot be decomposed into independent spectral modes.

